FDA has evaluated data in the petition and other relevant material and concludes that the proposed use of APH(3
')II as a processing aid in the development of new varieties of tomato, oilseed rape, and cotton is safe, and
that 21 CFR parts 173 and 573 should be amended as set forth below. 


